{"symbol": "FAM20B", "uniprot": "O75063", "protein_name": "Glycosaminoglycan xylosylkinase", "length": 409, "function": "Responsible for the 2-O-phosphorylation of xylose in the glycosaminoglycan-protein linkage region of proteoglycans thereby regulating the amount of mature GAG chains. Sulfated glycosaminoglycans (GAGs), including heparan sulfate and chondroitin sulfate, are synthesized on the so-called common GAG-protein linkage region (GlcUAbeta1-3Galbeta1-3Galbeta1-4Xylbeta1-O-Ser) of core proteins, which is formed by the stepwise addition of monosaccharide residues by the respective specific glycosyltransferases. Xylose 2-O-phosphorylation may influence the catalytic activity of B3GAT3 (GlcAT-I) which completes the precursor tetrasaccharide of GAG-protein linkage regions on which the repeating disaccharide region is synthesized", "ensembl_gene": "ENSG00000116199", "scores": {"selectivity": 0.4681, "protein_drug": 0.681, "rna_drug": 0.514}, "flags": {"surface": false, "enzyme": true, "mod_aso": false, "mod_sirna": false}, "details": {"nominated_modality": "Small molecule", "winning_axis": "protein", "quadrant": "Both viable", "best_route": "small molecule", "sm_score": "0.869", "sirna_score": "0.387", "aso_score": "0.419"}, "modality": "Small molecule", "structure": "data/structures/FAM20B.pdb", "pockets": [{"rank": 1, "druggability": 0.882, "volume": 756.6, "residues": [103, 109, 121, 123, 147, 162, 163, 165, 222, 223, 224, 225, 226, 227, 229, 230, 231, 294, 307, 308, 309, 310]}, {"rank": 2, "druggability": 0.026, "volume": 203.6, "residues": [396, 397, 399, 400, 401, 404, 405, 406, 408, 409]}, {"rank": 3, "druggability": 0.016, "volume": 271.4, "residues": [15, 16, 19, 20, 23]}], "links": [{"key": "uniprot", "label": "UniProt", "url": "https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb/O75063"}, {"key": "alphafold", "label": "AlphaFold", "url": "https://alphafold.ebi.ac.uk/entry/O75063"}, {"key": "opentargets", "label": "Open Targets", "url": "https://platform.opentargets.org/